- Saunders saturation calls
    - format: one entry per chapter when first-pass extraction completes
    - entry shape:
        - what came out of this chapter
        - what kinds of moves the chapter is about that did NOT make the gate
        - why those did not make it
        - decision: saturated | re-sweep needed

- Chapter 1: Front Matter (copyright, table of contents, epigraph)
    - what came out: nothing
    - what didn't make the gate: not applicable. The chapter is bibliographic metadata (copyright, TOC, an epigraph). It contains no teaching content from which moves could be extracted.
    - why: the chapter is structural front matter, not authorial argument or demonstration.
    - decision: saturated (vacuously, with zero skills)

- Chapter 2: We Begin
    - what came out: the-basic-drill, ask-strategic-not-interpretive, is-it-helping
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - keeping a small set of touchstone stories as a high bar (autobiographical aside, no concrete action)
        - workbook stance, going deeper than a first read allows (folded into the-basic-drill, which is the actual mechanism)
        - reading from the reader's experience as such (parent-context lens already captured in _book.md)
        - iconic space, resistance literature, rhetorical trial balloons (parent-context vocabulary already in _book.md; the only one that yielded an atomic move was the trial-balloon disposition, promoted as is-it-helping)
    - why: the chapter is mostly framing, lens-setting, and vocabulary already absorbed into _book.md as parent context. The three skills that survive each name a concrete reader/writer/teacher action with an observable signal and a recognizable failure mode, distinct from the lens itself. The dropped items are either vague or already covered.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 3: A Page at a Time
    - what came out: page-break-diagnostic, hollywood-version, cornfeld-principle, ritual-banality-avoidance, two-version-comparison, increasing-specification, truncation-test
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - bowling pins / juggler metaphor for tracking expectations (folded into page-break-diagnostic, which is the procedural form Saunders gives this idea)
        - structure as call-and-response between questions raised and answers supplied (folded into page-break-diagnostic for the same reason)
        - cross-painting characters with contradictory traits (folded into increasing-specification as one technique within the larger move)
        - variation against stasis when a beat repeats (dropped: action "vary it" too vague, no concrete signal that distinguishes good variation)
        - the motorcycle-and-sidecar metaphor for reader-writer closeness (dropped: evocative model rather than procedure, no concrete action or measurable signal)
        - "ruthless efficiency principle" as standalone (overlaps too tightly with cornfeld-principle, which is the procedural test the REP demands; folded by reference within cornfeld-principle's framing)
        - story-as-system-for-energy-transfer (dropped: a powerful image with no procedural form independent of the moves already promoted, especially ritual-banality-avoidance and truncation-test)
        - "Is it story yet?" as a slogan (folded into truncation-test, which is the actual mechanism for answering it)
    - why: this chapter is unusually rich because Saunders teaches by demonstrating multiple procedural moves in sequence on a single Chekhov story. Many candidates surfaced; the gate forced consolidation. Each promoted skill names a distinct situation and a distinct procedure, with no two doing the same work at different specificity. The dropped items are either evocative metaphors without independent procedural form (motorcycle/sidecar, energy transfer) or restatements of moves already promoted under sharper names (REP under cornfeld-principle, "Is it story yet?" under truncation-test, structure-as-call-and-response under page-break-diagnostic). Seven skills is at the upper end of the chapter's length budget but the chapter genuinely does the work to support each one.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 4: Afterthought #1
    - what came out: take-responsibility-for-every-element
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - the "Cat in the Rain" classroom recipe (folded: it is page-break-diagnostic + truncation-test packaged for a different story; no new procedural content)
        - the one-paragraph review of criticism as moment-by-moment noticing-and-articulating (folded into the-basic-drill, which is the procedural form)
        - Hemingway's "shockproof shit detector" (folded into the-basic-drill: a vivid name for the same trust-your-honest-reaction stance)
        - "an artist takes responsibility" as a standalone disposition (folded into take-responsibility-for-every-element, which operationalizes it)
    - why: this Afterthought is mostly recap and repackaging of the previous chapter's moves, plus one genuinely new application of the line-by-line lens to a film sequence. The recap content folds cleanly into existing skills under sharper procedural names. The Bicycle Thieves passage introduces something the prior chapter does not have a procedure for: an audit at the within-frame level (every element in a composed unit), which is finer-grained than cornfeld-principle (scene-level) and different in shape from two-version-comparison (audit what is there vs imagine what is not). The rest of the Afterthought is rhetorical reinforcement of the parent-context lens.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 5: The Singers (Turgenev source story)
    - what came out: none
    - what didn't make the gate: the chapter is Turgenev's story itself, not Saunders teaching. Visible structural features include the long village/pub framing before the action, the extended character portraits inserted between the buildup and the contest, the contrast between the contractor's technically dazzling first performance and Yashka's transcendent second performance, the narrator's choice to exit at the peak and return to find a deflated drunken aftermath, and the closing "Antropka!" call fading across the valley. Each is a teachable feature in principle, but the procedural form (action, observable signal, named failure mode) cannot be articulated honestly from the story alone without anticipating Chapter 6's commentary, which is out of scope for this pass.
    - why: source stories supply scenarios; teaching moves come from Saunders's commentary chapters. The right place for moves about narrative structure, character portraiture, and what Saunders calls "the heart of the story" is Chapter 6, which uses this story as its data.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 6: The Heart of the Story
    - what came out: track-non-normative-excesses, heart-of-the-story, panel-of-judges, holding-up-against-the-heart, energy-not-aspiration
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - "establishings, stabilizations, alterations" as a vocabulary for beat-tracking (folded into page-break-diagnostic; same beat-tracking the three-question protocol surfaces, restated in different terms)
        - "specificity makes character" and the contest-stakes formulation (A and B must stand for something) (folded into increasing-specification, which is the procedural form; Ch 6 sharpens its trigger to contest-shaped stories whose outcomes feel arbitrary)
        - the "20% then 10% more" cutting assignment (dropped: a teaching exercise without an observable signal that distinguishes good cutting from bad; the underlying ability "touch" is named but not operationalized; cornfeld-principle and take-responsibility-for-every-element supply the procedural tests for what to cut. Note: Appendix A is itself a cutting exercise and may surface a procedural skill on its own ground.)
        - "letting it stand" / final approval by sending out (folded into take-responsibility-for-every-element as its terminal stopping rule: the doorway image gives the audit's stop condition)
        - "Hollywood version" of "The Singers" (folded into hollywood-version as a second worked instance; Saunders here also clarifies that the Hollywood version is distinct from "the heart of the story," which is the new skill promoted)
    - why: this chapter is dense with new procedural moves because Saunders is teaching at the level of macro-structure (heart of story, panel of judges, holding up against), reader-side cataloging (TICHN), and writer-self-discovery (energy/voice). Five skills emerged. The folds are real refinements (Ch 6 supplies sharper triggers and worked instances for moves already promoted) rather than near-duplicates. The single drop is a classroom assignment that does not have the gate's procedural shape. Particular care was needed on heart-of-the-story vs. hollywood-version: Saunders himself distinguishes these in line 1690 ("The Hollywood version of 'The Singers' would be something like: 'Two men have a singing contest in a Russian pub. One wins, one loses.'" — versus "The heart of 'The Singers' is, of course, the singing contest"). The Hollywood version is the one-sentence story-shape used as a constraint on what the story is trying to be; the heart is the central scene/event the rest must route energy to. They fire in different revision moments and produce different decisions, so they are kept apart, with related: links to be set during finalization.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 7: Afterthought #2
    - what came out: iterative-preference-revision, respect-the-reader-cut
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - the line-level "Bob was an asshole" specification revision (folded into increasing-specification: same move applied to a single sentence rather than to a character introduction; Ch 7 sharpens the trigger to "a sentence that states a verdict instead of rendering the moment that produced it" and supplies the moral-ethical side-effect framing)
        - the disposition of trusting felt impulse during revision because each pass can revert the previous one (folded into iterative-preference-revision: this is the disposition the skill operationalizes, not a separate move)
        - the Stan-and-model-railroad image of art beginning in the instant of intuitive preference (folded into iterative-preference-revision: the chapter's opening illustration of the same move the skill operationalizes)
        - the apartment-redecoration analogy and the seed-crystal image for why iteration produces self-revealing work (folded into iterative-preference-revision: the analogies that motivate the procedure)
    - why: this Afterthought is autobiographical reflection on Saunders's own revision method. Two genuinely procedural moves emerge that the prior chapters do not give a procedure for: the iterative micro-revision practice driven by felt preference (the P/N meter), and the specific cutting test where an intelligent reader would supply what is being explained. The first is distinct from existing skills because no prior skill is about the act of self-revision itself (page-break-diagnostic surfaces expectations; cornfeld-principle and take-responsibility-for-every-element audit elements for function; truncation-test isolates ending work; none names the iterative reading-and-reacting practice). The second is distinct from take-responsibility-for-every-element because the test is not "does this element have a function" but "would the reader supply this for themselves from what is already on the page." The folds are real: the Bob example IS increasing-specification at sentence rather than character scope; the apartment, seed-crystal, and Stan images are illustrations of the iterative method, not separate moves. Two skills sits at the upper end of an Afterthought's length budget but the chapter genuinely supplies both procedures with worked examples.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 8: The Darling (Chekhov source story)
    - what came out: none
    - what didn't make the gate: visible features of the story include the four-attachment pattern (papa and aunt and French teacher in childhood, then the three husbands Kukin, Pustovalov, Smirnin, then finally the boy Sasha), the repeated mechanism by which Olenka adopts each partner's vocabulary and opinions as her own, the empty middle stretch when she has no attachment and consequently no opinions at all, the structural rhyme between the late-night telegram-knock that announces Kukin's death and the late-night knock at the close that turns out to be only the veterinary returning from the club, and the way the closing Sasha attachment is set apart from the prior three by the narrator's explicit comment that none of her former attachments was as deep. Procedural moves about repetition-as-pattern, character-identity-via-relationship, the differentiated-final-repetition shape, and the use of structural rhyme between knocks belong to Chapter 9's commentary (which Saunders titles "A Pattern Story") and are out of scope for this pass.
    - why: source stories supply scenarios; teaching moves come from Saunders's commentary chapters. The right place for moves about pattern stories and what merging-into-each-relationship reveals about character is Chapter 9, which uses this story as its data.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 9: A Pattern Story
    - what came out: parameter-table-for-recurrence, refuse-to-repeat-beats, skip-the-meaningless-interval
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - the optometrist's "Is this better, or this?" inflection-point pause and the Trot-rejection / Sasha-supplied move (folded into ritual-banality-avoidance: Saunders himself names this as the same Hanov-removal procedure from "In the Cart"; the new chapter sharpens the trigger to the inflection point and supplies the optometrist's framing)
        - the Mel/Dr. Bukhari sentence iteratively specified into a particular room, plus the slogan "in specificity lies nascent plot" (folded into increasing-specification: third worked instance, this one on a situation rather than a verdict; the chapter generalizes the trigger to whole-story specificity-precedes-plot reasoning, applied to Olenka's trait of becoming-whatever-she-loves)
        - the football-field-choreography analogy and the neutralized "9 on a scale of 10" counter-version (folded into parameter-table-for-recurrence: this is the motivating image for the parameter-tracking procedure; "internal dynamics" is what the parameter table makes visible)
        - the structural rhyme between the Kukin-death knock and the closing Smirnin-from-the-club knock (folded into parameter-table-for-recurrence: the rhyme is one row in the parameter schema, "ominous late-night gate event," that recurs and varies across the story; the underlying procedure is the same controlled-variation tracking)
        - "Then something happened that changed everything forever" as a way out of exposition (dropped: Saunders frames this explicitly as a joke; the genuine procedural move it gestures toward is captured by refuse-to-repeat-beats)
        - "walking around it from different angles" / "is this trait good or bad?" / Chekhov's answer "yes" (dropped: action too vague to produce an observable signal; the underlying procedural moves Saunders uses to achieve this — increasing-specification at the level of contradictory traits, holding-up-against-the-heart for ironic juxtaposition, refuse-to-repeat-beats for forcing each angle to add new information — are already covered; the closing meditation on world-making by ego and "infinite information" yielding mercy is parent-context resistance-literature material already in _book.md)
    - why: this chapter is unusually rich because Saunders teaches at the level of macro-structure (pattern recurrence, escalation, time-handling) and demonstrates each procedure on the full Olenka story. Three skills emerged. Each names a procedural shape that none of the prior 18 covers: parameter-table-for-recurrence (Saunders explicitly tabulates the four loves and reads across rows; existing skills are about single elements, single sentences, or static juxtaposition with the heart, not about controlled variation across recurrences); refuse-to-repeat-beats (existing skills treat scene-level cutting and ending-isolation, but none names the within-the-current-state diagnosis that asks "where is the next nudge that pushes us out of the just-changed condition"); skip-the-meaningless-interval (the skip-not-render move with the explicit story's-standard test; existing skills do not have a procedure for time-handling, only for prose-level cuts and scene-level audits). The folds are real: the optometrist pause IS the same first-order-removal move from "In the Cart," and Saunders cross-references it explicitly; the Mel sentence IS the same specification move at sentence scope; the football choreography IS what the parameter table makes visible; the structural-rhyme of the two knocks IS one parameter row in that table. The drops are either jokes (the "something happened that changed everything" line) or thematic outcomes already absorbed into _book.md (the closing meditation on world-making and mercy, which is Saunders's resistance-literature lens applied to his own reading of Olenka).
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 10: Afterthought #3
    - what came out: nothing (zero new skills)
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - the index-cards-on-a-date image and the Barthelme/Stern/Einstein triangulation about not merely executing the plan (folded into iterative-preference-revision: this is the disposition the iterative method operationalizes, restated in a new metaphor)
        - the Hot Wheels gas-stations metaphor for sentence-level propulsion and the "what are MY unique writerly charms?" question (dropped: the action — identify your unique charms — has no session-scope observable signal; Saunders himself frames the discovery as occurring across thousands of hours; the procedurally testable parts are mode-level decision (energy-not-aspiration) and sentence-level reaction (iterative-preference-revision), both already covered)
        - the "impersonate yourself reading the prose for the first time" formulation and the "evidence of care / less-cared-for versions" framing (folded into iterative-preference-revision: this is exactly the procedure that skill names; Ch 10 sharpens the self-impersonation framing and the reader-side intuition of discarded alternatives, but supplies no new procedure)
        - the "I can't complete the sentence, not in any general way... pencil in hand, on a given day" passage refusing a general theory of good prose (folded into iterative-preference-revision: the existing skill already refuses top-down rule-finding; this is the same anti-abstraction stance restated)
        - the "not there at the time of writing" diagnosis of an N-drop (folded into iterative-preference-revision: a reframe of why the needle drops, not a new procedure)
    - why: this Afterthought is the most explicitly recap-shaped of the three Afterthoughts. Its central claim — that revision is a practice of presence, conducted by reading your own prose as if it were new and reacting locally — is exactly what iterative-preference-revision (Afterthought #2) operationalizes. The chapter's gas-station, conversation-between-equals, and index-cards images are fresh metaphors for moves already promoted under their procedural names; none introduces an action with an observable signal that the prior Afterthought did not already provide. The one place the chapter gestures toward something genuinely new — the question "What makes MY reader keep reading?", the discovery of a writer's unique charms — Saunders explicitly stages as a lifelong artistic question rather than a session-scope procedure, with no observable signal short of "thousands of hours of work." Zero is the correct count for this chapter; it sits at the lower end of the 0-2 Afterthought budget. The chapter's value is dispositional reinforcement and metaphor-extension for the existing skills, all logged as folds.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 11: Master and Man (Tolstoy source story)
    - what came out: none
    - what didn't make the gate: visible structural features of the story include the patterned cycle of departures and arrivals across the snowstorm (Kresty departure, lost on the Zakharov fields, recovery at Grishkino, second departure with Petrushka as guide, lost again at the ravine, unharness and decision to stay the night, Vasili's solo flight on Mukhorty back into the storm), the literal sledge-circling in which Vasili rides in a circle and discovers his own hoofprints, the heavy accumulation of factual descriptive detail (Nikita's harnessing of Mukhorty, the welcome at Taras's house, the family talk of separation) before the freezing scene, the structural rhyme between Vasili's two attempts to light a cigarette in the storm, the framed contrast between Vasili's ruble-counting interior monologue and Nikita's acceptance of the Chief Master, the master's final reversal of warming Nikita with his own body, and the narrator's epilogue jump-forward that gives Nikita twenty more years and closes with the first-person plural "we shall all soon learn." Procedural moves about these features (Tolstoy's matrix of facts, repeated departures as escalation, the structural placement of the sacrificial reversal, the deferred-time epilogue) belong to Chapter 12 ("And Yet They Drove On"), out of scope here.
    - why: source stories supply scenarios; teaching moves come from Saunders's commentary chapters. The right place for moves about Tolstoy's fact-density, the controlled escalation of the snowstorm cycle, and the master's reversal is Chapter 12, which uses this story as its data.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 12: And Yet They Drove On (Thoughts on "Master and Man")
    - what came out: matrix-of-facts, mind-to-mind-vantage-shifts, causality-not-sequence, transformation-by-redirected-energy
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - the mansion-tour analogy and the "we're driving out to buy that land" announced organizing principle (folded into hollywood-version: the announced organizing principle is the same one-sentence shape the Hollywood version names, here extended to its in-story role for the reader; treating it as a separate skill would not add a new procedural move)
        - the "shadow structure" of section-level mini-arcs (each section opens with a setback and ends with dangled hope) (folded into parameter-table-for-recurrence: the shadow structure IS a parameter that recurs across all ten sections; the chapter sharpens the parameter-table procedure by encoding the shape of the unit itself, not just its contents, as a parameter row)
        - the four-times clothesline outside Grishkino and the place-setting / silverware-tracking-shot example (folded into parameter-table-for-recurrence: Saunders explicitly cross-references the Olenka chapter — "we defined escalation as that which results when we refuse to repeat beats" — and the procedure is identical, applied here to a recurring physical detail; the place-setting analogy is the most compressed worked instance of the move)
        - the structural-unit-as-Freytag's-triangle observation (folded into cornfeld-principle: this sharpens the second Cornfeld criterion ("advance the story in a non-trivial way") by giving it a procedural shape — the unit advances by enacting its own miniature arc; the fold note adds Freytag's-triangle-per-unit as the shape the second criterion implicitly demands)
        - the Section VI before-and-after of Vasili's failed coping methods (folded into parameter-table-for-recurrence: this is parameter-tracking applied to a single character across two passes through the same parameters; with two rows whose parameters fail uniformly in the second pass, the read-down is "this person has changed" — change made visible without being narrated)
        - Kundera on the suprapersonal wisdom of the novel and the writer-not-being-the-spokesman observation (dropped: this is a meditation on the disposition that makes craft possible, restated by Kundera and approved by Saunders, but its action ("open yourself to suprapersonal wisdom") has no observable session-scope signal beyond what existing skills already operationalize — iterative-preference-revision, energy-not-aspiration, mind-to-mind-vantage-shifts. The disposition is parent-context material for _book.md, not a procedure)
        - the wormwood as multivalent symbol (the chillingly egalitarian nature of death; identification between Vasili and the herb) (dropped: this is interpretive-mode close reading without a procedural form. The procedural moves Tolstoy uses to make the wormwood land — recurrence with controlled variation, factual rendering, holding-up-against-the-heart for the symbolic juxtaposition — are already covered by parameter-table-for-recurrence, matrix-of-facts, and holding-up-against-the-heart respectively)
        - Saunders's own plane-incident anecdote (dropped: it is autobiographical color used to triangulate the redirection-of-energy principle, already absorbed into transformation-by-redirected-energy as the worked-example variant)
        - the Scrooge / Joy-Hulga / Gatsby / Lear list of literary transformations (dropped: this is comparative scaffolding for the principle the new transformation skill operationalizes; treating it as a separate skill would name a phenomenon (characters change in stories) without supplying an action distinct from what transformation-by-redirected-energy already gives)
    - why: this chapter is dense with teaching moves at multiple levels — prose register (matrix-of-facts), narrative-distance protocol (mind-to-mind-vantage-shifts), beat-to-beat construction (causality-not-sequence), and climactic-scene shape (transformation-by-redirected-energy). Four skills emerged, each procedurally distinct from the prior 21. The folds are real and Saunders himself flags most of them: the clothesline is named as the "refusal-to-repeat" move from the Olenka chapter; the shadow structure and Section-VI before/after are both parameter-table phenomena where the parameter-table can encode shapes and pass-counts; the Freytag's-triangle-per-unit observation refines the second Cornfeld criterion without naming a new test; the announced-organizing-principle in-story is the reader-side version of the Hollywood version. The drops are either dispositional material (Kundera's suprapersonal wisdom, parent-context for _book.md), interpretive close reading without procedural form (the wormwood meditation), worked example for an already-extracted skill (the plane anecdote), or comparative scaffolding without a distinct action (the Scrooge / Lear / Gatsby list). Four is the right count: this is the Tolstoy commentary chapter and Saunders is teaching at full strength, but no fifth procedure has the action / signal / failure-mode shape the gate requires that the existing 21 + 4 don't already cover.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 13: Afterthought #4
    - what came out: convert-moral-critique-to-technical
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - the parallel-moments audit (granting equal narrative resources to characters in parallel structural positions) (folded into convert-moral-critique-to-technical: this is the operationalization of the conversion when the moral concern is character bias; the parallel-moments check is the conversion's core procedure, not a separate move. Treating it as its own skill would create a near-duplicate firing whenever the conversion fires for bias-shaped accusations)
        - the twenty-years-later / unchanged-savee test (after a sacrifice, follow the saved party forward to check whether their later actions register the event) (folded into convert-moral-critique-to-technical: the chapter uses the unchanged Nikita as the diagnostic that surfaces the denied-interiority problem, and Saunders's "It also makes us wonder about the writer" line lands the technical-not-moral framing. Treating the unchanged-savee as its own skill would fragment the chapter's single new teaching, which is the conversion procedure of which the downstream check is one piece)
        - the corrective exercise (write the rebalanced version of Section X granting Nikita interiority equal to Vasili's; "Write it like Tolstoy. Use, you know, a lot of facts.") (folded into two-version-comparison: this is the existing two-version-comparison move applied to a corrected version of an inequitable passage rather than to a craft choice whose effect you cannot articulate; the procedure is identical and the new skill references this fold as its verification step)
    - why: this Afterthought is a single, sustained teaching: a moral failing in a story will, on examination, manifest as a technical failing — most commonly inequitable narration — and converting the moral verdict into the technical observation produces a fix the writer can apply, while leaving the critic's noticing intact. The single skill that survives names this conversion as a procedure (refuse the verdict and the dismissal, ask "where exactly," locate the inequity, audit parallel moments, follow downstream, write the corrected version, state the fix as a craft instruction). The folds are real and reflect the chapter's structure: the parallel-moments audit is the central operationalization, the unchanged-savee diagnosis is the chapter's worked instance of how the inequity surfaces, and the rewrite-Section-X exercise is the existing two-version-comparison move applied to a corrected version. There is one skill here because the chapter teaches one thing: how to convert a moral observation into a technical one. The 25 prior skills do not cover this — mind-to-mind-vantage-shifts is about within-scene rotation of vantage among present characters; ask-strategic-not-interpretive shifts the question type but not from moral to technical; two-version-comparison is for unnameable craft effects rather than for moral effects converted to inequitable technique. One skill is the right count for this Afterthought, well within the 0-2 length budget.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 14: The Nose (Gogol source story)
    - what came out: none
    - what didn't make the gate: visible features of the story include the absurdist register that treats the disappeared nose as a plain fact requiring bureaucratic redress, the inflated ranks-and-titles vocabulary (Collegiate Assessor, state councillor, field officer's wife) invoked at every social moment, the Nose appearing in uniform as a person of higher rank than its owner at Kazan Cathedral, the narrator's two explicit refusals to explain the chain of events (the bridge-policeman scene "shrouded in mist", the close of Section II "shrouded in fog"), the embedded exchange of letters between Kovalyov and Mrs. Podtochina, the comic mismatch between the metaphysical strangeness of the disappearance and the petty social calculations it provokes (whom Kovalyov can no longer call on, marriage prospects, the newspaper-office advertisement), and the narrator's closing self-interrogation that audibly admits the tale makes no sense and ends "such things happen in this world; rarely, but they do." Procedural moves about those features (absurdist register, treating-the-strange-as-fact, bureaucratic hierarchy as comic engine, the structural use of unexplained gaps, the narrator's closing confession) belong to Chapter 15 ("The Door to the Truth Might Be Strangeness"), out of scope here.
    - why: source stories supply scenarios; teaching moves come from Saunders's commentary chapters.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 15: The Door to the Truth Might Be Strangeness (Thoughts on "The Nose")
    - what came out: psychological-physics-of-strangeness, multiple-superimposed-weirdness, skaz-narrator, improper-narrative-emphasis, confess-the-oddness
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - the two-cartoon-bubbles model of communication (Doug Unger, plus the Hollywood-agent-and-farmer story) (folded into mind-to-mind-vantage-shifts: the existing skill rotates vantage among present characters during morally loaded exchanges; the bubble-preload step sharpens the procedure for the case where the load comes from each character bringing unrelated private content rather than from one character lying about a shared subject. Treating it as a separate skill would near-duplicate mind-to-mind whenever it fires for a miscommunication-shaped scene)
        - the surrender-to-natural-mode model of writing (the two models — strive upward toward James-style precision vs. surrender to natural mode and refine within its grain; the corporate-poem worked example; "every soul is vast and wants to express itself fully... out comes poetry, i.e., truth forced out through a restricted opening"; the fence-of-language image; Pevear and Sinyavsky on Gogol creating a medium "not imitative of the natural speech of educated men" by resorting to "the inability to speak in an ordinary way") (folded into energy-not-aspiration: the existing skill names the choice as energy-vs-aspiration; this chapter adds the post-abandonment procedure — once the aspirational mode is let go, the work is concentrated refinement within the natural mode rather than a re-stretch toward the original aspiration. Treating it as a separate skill would split the energy-vs-aspiration disposition from the procedure that completes it)
        - the unchanged-protagonist ending (Kovalyov returns to his pre-event self; the medical-test analogy; the explicit Vasili-vs-Kovalyov contrast — "Like Vasili, Kovalyov gets a foretaste of death... But unlike Vasili, Kovalyov doesn't take the hint") (folded into transformation-by-redirected-energy: the existing skill addresses how to write a moral transformation when one is happening; this chapter adds the contrast condition — when the character is constituted such that they will not change, the right move is the unchanged-protagonist ending. Treating this as a separate skill would create a contrasts-pair without a distinct procedure beyond "consider whether the character must change"; folding it into the transformation skill installs the diagnosis question — is this person the kind who would register this hint or proceed past it? — at the right place in the workflow)
        - the joy-burst exception to the Cornfeld principle (the newspaper-office passage where "a group of people waiting to place ads get transformed into that for which they are advertising"; "what makes Gogol great, that he somehow felt inclined to do that, and then did it, with such strange, happy confidence... not essential to the action of the story but seems to have been done just for the fun of it") (folded into cornfeld-principle: the existing skill names two criteria a passage must meet to earn its place; this chapter adds an explicit exception condition — a passage that produces a marked uptick of reader-side fondness/delight and was clearly written from the writer's pleasure rather than from plot necessity is allowed to stay even when it fails both criteria. The exception is narrow; treating joy-burst as its own skill would name an exception without supplying a distinct procedure beyond "in this case, override Cornfeld")
        - the absurdism-as-realism reframe ("Gogol is sometimes referred to as an absurdist... But to me, Gogol is a supreme realist, looking past the way things seem to how they really are"; the scrim-drops-and-the-open-ocean metaphor) (dropped: this is the orientation that licenses the strange-event-physics skill, with no session-scope action distinct from "use the strange-event-physics skill." Folded as orienting context into psychological-physics-of-strangeness's framing rather than as its own skill)
        - the Akakii Akakievich / "Crap P. Poopton" anecdote about translation losses (lines 5376-5384) (dropped: the chapter uses it to acknowledge the limits of teaching from a translated text; it has no procedural form)
        - the Nabokov / Gogol-biography material on Gogol's strangeness as a person, his late mysticism, his loss of the splitting gift (lines 5412-5436) (dropped: comparative biographical color used to triangulate the writer-watching-the-banal-man-within framing, already absorbed into energy-not-aspiration as the surrender-to-natural-mode fold; treating it as a separate skill would name a phenomenon without supplying an action with an observable signal)
        - the political reading (Klemperer / Memoirs of an Anti-Semite / Gogol-as-narrator-of-the-Holocaust passages, lines 5512-5527) (dropped: this is the chapter's interpretive coda extending the skaz-loops principle to political pathology, recognizable as parent-context resistance-literature framing already in _book.md; the procedure for surfacing the same pathology in a draft is mind-to-mind-vantage-shifts plus convert-moral-critique-to-technical, both already extracted)
    - why: this chapter is the densest commentary chapter in the book, containing five procedurally distinct teaching moves each operating at a different level of craft. (1) The strange-event-as-premise-with-meaning-in-the-response operationalizes a whole genre-orientation move (psychological-physics-of-strangeness). (2) The compounding of weirdness across categories names a structural escalation move distinct from the existing refuse-to-repeat-beats (multiple-superimposed-weirdness; the categories are weirdness-categories, not beats). (3) The unreliable-narrator-as-character with deliberate misfires names a voice technique distinct from any prior skill (skaz-narrator; the narrator is a character whose failures the writer controls). (4) The deflection-via-emphasis names a sentence-level tactic distinct from any prior skill (improper-narrative-emphasis; sidestep the unrenderable). (5) The closing confession that acknowledges without resolving names an ending move distinct from the existing truncation-test (confess-the-oddness; the oddness is acknowledged but the gaps remain). Five is the right count for this chapter — the highest of any commentary chapter — because the chapter teaches at five distinct levels (genre orientation, structural escalation, voice, sentence-level deflection, ending). The folds are real and Saunders himself frames most of them as extensions of prior moves: the cartoon-bubbles model is the everyday version of the mind-to-mind technique; the surrender-to-natural-mode is the post-abandonment phase of the energy-not-aspiration choice; the unchanged-protagonist is the contrast condition for transformation-by-redirected-energy; the joy-burst is an exception to the Cornfeld principle. The drops are the orientation framing (absurdism-as-realism, parent-context for the strange-event skill), comparative biographical color (Nabokov, late Gogol), translation acknowledgments (Akakii Akakievich), and political coda (Klemperer, Memoirs of an Anti-Semite) — none of which have session-scope actions distinct from the existing or new skills. Five is at the upper end of the budget but the chapter's density and Saunders's explicit naming of distinct techniques justifies it.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 16: Afterthought #5
    - what came out: follow-the-voice
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - the voice-expansion-by-novel-events principle ("if a character has never seen a horse before, and I show him one, his voice has to expand") (folded into follow-the-voice: this is the escalation engine that keeps a voice-led draft generative; treating it as a separate skill would split the method from its engine. The horse example is the worked instance of step 5 of the new skill. Refuse-to-repeat-beats is procedurally adjacent — refuse to elaborate on a recently-arrived state — but its trigger is scene-pacing in revision, not voice-led drafting; the voice-expansion engine is the drafting-time form of the same anti-stasis principle and lives inside follow-the-voice)
        - voice as essential part of truth, not embellishment (the honey/milk LI 34321 passage and the morning-walking-out passage; "voice is not just an embellishment; it's an essential part of the truth"; "love has fallen on a particular, goofy person... that morning has to fall on a certain mind for it to feel like any kind of real morning") (folded into follow-the-voice: the orientation that licenses the method, installed in the new skill's "When to reach for this" and the failure-mode section. The honey/milk and walking-out-the-house passages are the worked instances of the orientation. Treating it as a separate skill would name a disposition with no session-scope procedure distinct from the new skill's procedure)
        - the black-box framing of story as state-change device, the archery release metaphor, and the carnival-barker / roller-coaster-designer contrast with the stressed-engineer (lines 5722-5732 and 5790-5806) (folded into iterative-preference-revision: the existing skill names the anti-top-down stance and the locality of decision; this Afterthought adds three sharper metaphors — the black box, the archery release, the carnival barker / roller-coaster designer — that motivate the same stance. The roller-coaster designer's procedure is exactly the iterative-preference-revision procedure restated as apparatus design: attend to the local intensity-maximizing decision; do not specify the reader's reaction in advance. The fold adds the freeze-up failure mode in its train-engineer form)
        - the broader generalization that "follow the voice" is one of many methods (recurring imagery, the look of words on the page, sound, structural minutiae are other engines) (folded into follow-the-voice: the broader principle is named in the new skill's "When to reach for this" as the abstract category, with voice as the worked instance and the other engines named explicitly. Treating it as its own skill would yield a near-tautological action with no observable signal beyond what the voice-led instance already provides)
    - why: this Afterthought teaches one new procedural move at full strength — a generative drafting method in which the writer begins from a voice fragment and lets world, plot, and theme emerge as byproducts of voice-sustaining. None of the prior 31 skills cover this. Energy-not-aspiration names the one-time decision of which mode to commit to (the voice you have energy in vs. the voice you wanted to have); follow-the-voice is the per-draft generative method (sit down at a blank page; find a voice fragment; sustain it; let escalation force the world). Iterative-preference-revision is a revision practice (read the existing prose, react locally, fix); follow-the-voice is a drafting initiation practice (no prose yet, find a voice fragment that will produce some). Skaz-narrator is about what a narrator's voice does for the meaning of the story; follow-the-voice is the writer's procedure for finding any voice in the first place. The folds are real and reflect the chapter's structure: the voice-expansion-by-novel-events is the drafting-time engine inside the new skill (and a drafting-time analog of refuse-to-repeat-beats); the voice-as-truth orientation licenses the new skill's procedure; the broader-methods generalization names follow-the-voice as one instance of a wider category. The black-box / archery / carnival-barker metaphors are fresh motivations for iterative-preference-revision's existing anti-top-down stance, with the carnival-barker / engineer contrast adding the train-engineer freeze-up as a third failure mode in the existing skill. One promoted skill is the right count for this Afterthought, well within the 0-2 length budget — the chapter teaches a single procedure at length and supplies its complete worked instance ("Jon" generated from a student-paper sentence).
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 17: Gooseberries (Chekhov source story)
    - what came out: none
    - what didn't make the gate: visible features of the story include the frame-and-tale structure (Burkin and Ivan Ivanych caught in the rain, taking shelter at Alyohin's, where Ivan Ivanych delivers his embedded tale of his brother Nikolay), Ivan Ivanych's exuberant swim in the rain as a moment of character-disclosure between the discomfort of arrival and the comfort of the upstairs drawing room, the recurrence of Pelageya the chambermaid as a silent presence registered with a glance by both visitors, the controlled-variation visual of Alyohin's bathwater (brown, then ink-blue), the embedded story's escalation from clerk's daydream to starved widow to coffee-colored stream and sour-but-pronounced-delicious gooseberries, the Pushkin couplet positioned as the brother's self-deception articulated in literary form, the interpolated cattle-dealer-with-leg and merchant-eating-money-with-honey anecdotes inserted mid-tale, the "man with a hammer" image that is the embedded tale's didactic peak, the deflationary frame-close in which the listeners are unsatisfied and want to talk about elegant women instead, the structural irony that Ivan Ivanych delivers an anti-comfort sermon then luxuriates in clean linen in a rich man's drawing room, the asymmetric weight of the frame's opening landscape sentence (factual register building the plain, hills, willows, telegraph poles), and the closing image of the rain beating against the window panes all night. Procedural moves about these features (frame-and-tale construction, the embedded didactic peak as climactic image, the deflationary close that refuses to honor the speaker's sermon, the structural irony of the preacher in the drawing room, the matrix-of-facts opening, the Pushkin-couplet self-deception positioned beside the hard-sour gooseberries, the cumulative cleansing-arc from mud-cross-and-uncomfortable to fragrant clean linen) belong to Chapter 18 ("A Swim in a Pond in the Rain: Thoughts on 'Gooseberries'", lines 5939-6403), out of scope here.
    - why: source stories supply scenarios; teaching moves come from Saunders's commentary chapters. The right place for moves about the frame-and-tale form, the deflationary close, and the structural irony of the sermon delivered then betrayed by its setting is Chapter 18, which uses this story as its data.
    - decision: saturated

- Chapter 18: A Swim in a Pond in the Rain (Thoughts on "Gooseberries")
    - what came out: persistent-self-contradiction, belief-by-character-attribution
    - what didn't make the gate:
        - the pop-out test on the rain digression (cut a section from the middle, observe whether the seam is visible, log the unit on the TICHN cart with the deferred question "what were you for?") (folded into truncation-test: the existing skill cuts the end and asks "is it story yet?"; this chapter extends the same cut-and-observe procedure to internal structural units, with the question reshaped from "is it story yet" to "what was this unit for?" The fold note adds the pop-out variant as a second mode of the same skill, with the seamless-cut as data rather than verdict, and the read-forward-with-cart-in-mind as the redemption procedure)
        - the heart-of-the-heart recursion (when the heart is itself a multi-element scene, the audit recurses; the heart of "Gooseberries" is Ivan's anecdote, the heart of that anecdote is Ivan's speech) plus the Seussian "Why are you bothering telling me this?" formulation (folded into heart-of-the-story: Saunders explicitly names "the heart of the heart of the story" and runs the same audit at the inner layer; the fold installs the recursion as step 3 of the existing procedure and adds the Seussian question as a fresh restatement of the heart-finding question)
        - the smelly-pipe reveal at the close of "Gooseberries" (a small concrete late detail that does not refute the speech but, by attribution to the character who delivered it, makes the speech read differently on rereading; the reader's back-scan; the discovery of countervailing material like the swimming scene; "the two readings coexist, making a truth bigger than either would have alone") (folded into belief-by-character-attribution: the smelly pipe is the worked instance of the destabilizing-detail step in the new skill's procedure; treating it as its own skill would split the destabilizing detail from the speech-attribution procedure that licenses it. The back-scan is named as step 6 of the new skill, where the writer plants countervailing material in advance so the reader can find it)
        - the digression-free counterfactual of "Gooseberries" (Saunders writes out the version of the story without the digression and lists what is lost; "an unchallenged lecture from Ivan with a simple takeaway: Happiness — not as great as you think") (folded into two-version-comparison: the existing skill writes the inverted version of a sentence-level / scene-level craft choice; this chapter scales the same procedure to a structural unit. The fold note: the comparison can scale up to whole sections; the test on a digression is "what specific complications does the digression-free version lose, and is the loss the story collapsing into lecture?")
        - the author-disposition material on Chekhov as "free of agenda... willing to go wherever the data takes him"; "if he has a program, it's being wary of having a program"; stories as "splendid, brief reconsideration machines" (lines 6299-6313) (folded into persistent-self-contradiction: the disposition that licenses the procedure, installed in the new skill's source note and framing. Treating it as a separate skill would name a stance with no session-scope action distinct from the new skill's procedure)
        - the inner-orchestra image (any idea we express is one of many we have within us; writing is the chance to change the mix; every person has the same instruments in their inner orchestra) (lines 6363-6369) (folded into belief-by-character-attribution: the orientation that licenses the new skill's "export fragments of yourself" procedure, installed as the inner-orchestra orientation in the new skill's source note and framing)
        - the meta-acknowledgment that the digression-justifies-itself claim is "tautological, since the digression is pretty much all the story is" (lines 6243-6245) (dropped: this is a self-aware caveat about the worked example, not a procedural move. Saunders's note that he might "seem to be implying something... about how the story was written" — that Chekhov first wrote Ivan's speech and then framed it — is a useful disclaimer about reverse-engineering published work but has no session-scope action)
        - the closing biographical anecdote about Tolstoy and Chekhov swimming together at Yasnaya Polyana (lines 6377-6387) (dropped: this is a closing literary frame for the chapter that mirrors the swimming scene in "Gooseberries"; it has no procedural form and is autobiographical color rather than a teaching move. The fact that Chekhov played both Burkin and Ivan in the swim is interpretive observation, not a procedure)
        - the closing footnote *2 on extremism (lines 6398-6403): "Let's decide, for example, that the story isn't about happiness but extremism — guess what? It is. Look at how many extremists are in it..." (dropped: this is Saunders demonstrating that the persistent-self-contradiction structure can be re-read with "extremism" or "duty" or "passion" or "suppression" as the central concern and still hold; it is a confirmation of the new skill, not a separate move. The "try the same trick with other notions" framing is folded as orientation into persistent-self-contradiction's failure-mode wording: the skill should be applicable regardless of which thematic concern the writer chooses to organize the contradictions around, and a story that has been correctly self-contradicted will hold under multiple thematic re-readings)
        - "A story means, at the highest level, not by what it concludes but by how it proceeds" (line 6257) (dropped: a vivid summary of the disposition that produces persistent-self-contradiction. The procedure that operationalizes the disposition is the new skill; treating the slogan as its own skill would name a maxim without a procedure)
    - why: this chapter is the title-essay commentary on Chekhov's "Gooseberries" and Saunders teaches at the level of a single procedural shape — how to make a story that has a thematic charge avoid becoming polemic — but reaches that single shape through two complementary procedures: persistent self-contradiction at the macro-structural level (each aspect that votes for a position has a counterweight aspect that complicates it; the chain recurses; the story qualifies itself out of judgment) and belief-by-character-attribution at the speech-handling level (a sincere belief is delivered with full conviction by a character; the writer steps back; the story reacts to the speaker's flaws via a small concrete destabilizing detail; both readings coexist). The two skills are procedurally distinct: persistent-self-contradiction is a macro-structural method for handling theme across a whole story, applied to aspects (characters, scenes, images, voices) that vote for or against a position; belief-by-character-attribution is a speech-handling method for handling a single concentrated articulation of belief, applied to a particular speech delivered by a particular character. They commonly fire together (in "Gooseberries" they do), but they fire on different surfaces and at different scales, so a story can have one without the other. The folds are real and reflect the chapter's structure: the pop-out test extends truncation-test to internal units; the heart-of-the-heart recursion extends heart-of-the-story to multi-layer hearts; the smelly-pipe reveal is the destabilizing-detail step inside belief-by-character-attribution; the digression-free counterfactual is two-version-comparison at structural scale; the Chekhov-disposition material is the orientation that licenses persistent-self-contradiction; the inner-orchestra image is the orientation that licenses belief-by-character-attribution. The drops are self-aware caveats (the tautology disclaimer), biographical color (the Tolstoy-Chekhov swim), and demonstrations that the new skill works on multiple thematic re-readings (the extremism footnote). Two is the right count for this commentary chapter — well within the 2-5 budget — because the chapter teaches one master subject (how a story holds a thematic charge without becoming polemic) through two procedurally distinct methods (the macro and the speech-handling), and Saunders himself separates them in the chapter's structure (the persistent-self-contradiction discussion in lines 6256-6313, the belief-handling discussion in lines 6321-6369). Folding both into one skill would conflate procedures that fire on different surfaces; treating them as one would violate the gate's "novel" criterion in the wrong direction (one skill instead of two). The 26 prior skills do not cover either: heart-of-the-story finds the central event, holding-up-against-the-heart juxtaposes static elements with the heart, parameter-table-for-recurrence tracks variation across recurrences, mind-to-mind-vantage-shifts rotates among present characters in a single morally loaded scene, transformation-by-redirected-energy handles climactic character change, skaz-narrator handles a graceless narrator-character whose register is itself the meaning. None of these supplies either the macro-structural counterweight-pairing procedure or the sincere-belief-as-character-speech procedure.
    - decision: saturated
